
# Opening and compiling in MPLABX

## First

- Clone repository
- Update paths in [project config](nbproject/project.xml) to reflect new locations

## IDE

Written using Microchip MPLABX v6.15. Downloads for:

- [Windows](https://ww1.microchip.com/downloads/aemDocuments/documents/DEV/ProductDocuments/SoftwareTools/MPLABX-v6.20-windows-installer.exe)
- [Linux](https://ww1.microchip.com/downloads/aemDocuments/documents/DEV/ProductDocuments/SoftwareTools/MPLABX-v6.20-linux-installer.tar)

## Compiler

Last version of the XC16 compiler to include `itoa` is version v1.70.

Downloads:

- [Windows](https://ww1.microchip.com/downloads/en/DeviceDoc/xc16-v1.70-full-install-windows64-installer.exe)
- [Linux](https://ww1.microchip.com/downloads/en/DeviceDoc/xc16-v1.70-full-install-linux64-installer.run)

## Device pack

1.8.217 for the PIC24FJ128GB204
